----->\n|postal_code_type       =  [[Postal code of China|Postal code]] \n|postal_code            = 030600\n|area_code              = 0354\n|blank_name             =<!-- [[GDP]] -->\n|blank_info             = \n|blank1_name            =<!-- GDP per capita -->\n|blank1_info            =\n|blank2_name             =[[Vehicle registration plates of China|Licence plates]]\n|blank2_info             ={{lang|zh-cn|\u664bK}}\n|blank3_name            =[[Administrative division codes of the People's Republic of China|Administrative division code]] \n|blank3_info            =140700\n|iso_code = [[ISO 3166-2:CN|CN-SX-07]]\n|website                = {{URL|sxjz.gov.cn/}}\n|footnotes              = \n}} \n{{Infobox Chinese\n|s={{linktext|\u664b\u4e2d}} |t={{linktext|\u6649\u4e2d}} |p=J\u00ecnzh\u014dng |w=Chin-chung |l=Central{{nbsp}}Jin\n}}\n{{Infobox Chinese\n|title=Yuci\n|c={{linktext|\u6986\u6b21}} |p=Y\u00fac\u00ec |w=Yu-tz\u2018u |l=[[Elm (tree)|Elm]]{{nbsp}}Place \n}}\n'''Jinzhong''',<!--Chinese in infobox; see WP:MOS-ZH--> formerly '''Yuci''', is a [[prefecture-level city]] with 3.2 million inhabitants at the 2010 census in east central [[Shanxi]] province of the [[People's Republic of China]], bordering [[Hebei]] province to the east.\n\n==History==\n[[Lingshi County]] was the location of the [[Nanshan Colliery disaster]].\n\nIn 1999, the area was considered sufficiently [[urbanization|urbanized]] that Jinzhong [[Prefecture (China)|Prefecture]] became a [[prefecture-level city]], with its former seat at Yuci becoming its [[county-level district|county-level]] [[Yuci District]].\n\n==Administrative divisions==\nJinzhong is divided into the following county-level subdivisions:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"font-size:90%;\" align=center\n!colspan=\"6\" align=\"center\" | Map\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" align=\"center\" | <div style=\"position: relative\" class=\"center\">\n{{Image label begin|image=Administrative Division Jinzhong.png|width=650|link=}} \n{{Image label|x=1270|y=540|scale=650/2600|text=[[Yuci District|'''Yuci''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=1200|y=820|scale=650/2600|text=[[Taigu District|'''Taigu''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=1400|y=1160|scale=650/2600|text=[[Yushe County|'''Yushe<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=1910|y=1260|scale=650/2600|text=[[Zuoquan County|'''Zuoquan<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=1900|y=880|scale=650/2600|text=[[Heshun County|'''Heshun<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=2140|y=630|scale=650/2600|text=[[Xiyang County|'''Xiyang<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=1590|y=330|scale=650/2600|text=[[Shouyang County|'''Shouyang<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=980|y=970|scale=650/2600|text=[[Qi County, Shanxi|'''Qi<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=770|y=1130|scale=650/2600|text=[[Pingyao County|'''Pingyao<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=260|y=1490|scale=650/2600|text=[[Lingshi County|'''Lingshi<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=490|y=1270|scale=650/2600|text=[[Jiexiu|'''Jiexiu<br>{{small|(city)}}''']]}}\n</div>\n|-\n! Name\n! [[Hanzi]]\n! [[Hanyu Pinyin]]\n! Population (2003 est.)\n! Area (km\u00b2)\n! Density (/km\u00b2)\n|-\n|[[Yuci District]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u6986\u6b21\u533a}}\n|Y\u00fac\u00ec Q\u016b\n|530,000\n|1,327\n|399\n|-\n|[[Taigu District]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u592a\u8c37\u533a}}\n|T\u00e0ig\u01d4 Q\u016b\n|280,000\n|1,034\n|271\n|-\n|[[Jiexiu|Jiexiu City]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u4ecb\u4f11\u5e02}}\n|Ji\u00e8xi\u016b Sh\u00ec\n|380,000\n|743\n|511\n|-\n|[[Yushe County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u6986\u793e\u53bf}}\n|Y\u00fash\u00e8 Xi\u00e0n\n|140,000\n|1,651\n|85\n|-\n|[[Zuoquan County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u5de6\u6743\u53bf}}\n|Zu\u01d2qu\u00e1n Xi\u00e0n\n|160,000\n|2,028\n|79\n|-\n|[[Heshun County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u548c\u987a\u53bf}}\n|H\u00e9sh\u00f9n Xi\u00e0n\n|140,000\n|2,251\n|62\n|-\n|[[Xiyang County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u6614\u9633\u53bf}}\n|X\u012by\u00e1ng Xi\u00e0n\n|230,000\n|1,943\n|118\n|-\n|[[Shouyang County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u5bff\u9633\u53bf}}\n|Sh\u00f2uy\u00e1ng Xi\u00e0n\n|210,000\n|2,111\n|99\n|-\n|[[Qi County, Shanxi|Qi County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u7941\u53bf}}\n|Q\u00ed Xi\u00e0n\n|260,000\n|854\n|304\n|-\n|[[Pingyao County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u5e73\u9065\u53bf}}\n|P\u00edngy\u00e1o Xi\u00e0n\n|490,000\n|1,260\n|389\n|-\n|[[Lingshi County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u7075\u77f3\u53bf}}\n|L\u00edngsh\u00ed Xi\u00e0n\n|240,000\n|1,206\n|199\n|}\n\n==Climate==\nJinzhong has a continental, [[monsoon]]-influenced [[semi-arid climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|K\u00f6ppen]] ''BSk''),<ref>Peel, M. C., Finlayson, B. L., and McMahon, T. A.: Updated world map of the K\u00f6ppen-Geiger climate classification, Hydrol. Earth Syst. Sci., 11, 1633-1644, doi:10.5194/hess-11-1633-2007, 2007.</ref> with cold and very dry winters, and hot, humid summers. The monthly 24-hour average temperature ranges from {{convert|\u22125.5|\u00b0C|1}} in January to {{convert|24.2|\u00b0C}} in July, and the annual mean is {{convert|10.39|\u00b0C|1}}. Typifying the influence of the [[East Asian Monsoon]], over two-thirds of the annual {{convert|388|mm}} of precipitation occurs from June to September.\n\n{{Weather box\n| width = auto \n| metric first = Y\n| single line  = Y\n| location     = Jinzhong (Yuci District), 1981&ndash;2010\n| Jan high C  =  1.9 \n| Feb high C  =  5.8 \n| Mar high C  = 11.9 \n| Apr high C  = 20.0 \n| May high C  = 25.6 \n| Jun high C  = 29.3 \n| Jul high C  = 30.4 \n| Aug high C  = 28.5 \n| Sep high C  = 24.1 \n| Oct high C  = 17.9 \n| Nov high C  =  9.7 \n| Dec high C  =  3.2\n\n| Jan mean C  = \u22125.5 \n| Feb mean C  = \u22121.5 \n| Mar mean C  =  4.6 \n| Apr mean C  = 12.6 \n| May mean C  = 18.5 \n| Jun mean C  = 22.4 \n| Jul mean C  = 24.2 \n| Aug mean C  = 22.4 \n| Sep mean C  = 17.3 \n| Oct mean C  = 10.7 \n| Nov mean C  =  2.7 \n| Dec mean C  = \u22123.7\n\n| Jan low C  = \u221211.2 \n| Feb low C  =  \u22127.4 \n| Mar low C  =  \u22121.6 \n| Apr low C  =   5.4 \n| May low C  =  11.4 \n| Jun low C  =  15.9 \n| Jul low C  =  18.9 \n| Aug low C  =  17.4 \n| Sep low C  =  11.8 \n| Oct low C  =   4.9 \n| Nov low C  =  \u22122.7 \n| Dec low C  =  \u22128.9 \n| precipitation colour  = green\n| Jan precipitation mm  =  2.0 \n| Feb precipitation mm  =  3.3 \n| Mar precipitation mm  =  9.9 \n| Apr precipitation mm  = 21.0 \n| May precipitation mm  = 37.2 \n| Jun precipitation mm  = 52.2 \n| Jul precipitation mm  = 81.9 \n| Aug precipitation mm  = 87.8 \n| Sep precipitation mm  = 54.0 \n| Oct precipitation mm  = 27.0 \n| Nov precipitation mm  =  9.9 \n| Dec precipitation mm  =  1.7 \n|Jan humidity = 47\n|Feb humidity = 45\n|Mar humidity = 44\n|Apr humidity = 42\n|May humidity = 48\n|Jun humidity = 56\n|Jul humidity = 67\n|Aug humidity = 71\n|Sep humidity = 69\n|Oct humidity = 62\n|Nov humidity = 55\n|Dec humidity = 50\n| source = China Meteorological Administration<ref name=\"cma graphical\">{{cite web\n|url=http://data.cma.cn/data/weatherBk.html\n|script-title=zh:\u4e2d\u56fd\u6c14\u8c61\u6570\u636e\u7f51 - WeatherBk Data\n|publisher=[[China Meteorological Administration]]\n|accessdate=2018-11-09}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Transportation==\n*[[Taiyuan\u2013Jiaozuo Railway]]\n\n== Culture ==\nThe [[prefecture-level city]] houses several [[Shanxi Courtyard Houses]], businessmen's residences lauded as outstanding civilian residences.\n\n[[Yuci District]] is increasingly connected to nearby [[Taiyuan]], whose built-up area was home to 3,848,151 people [[2010 Chinese census|in 2010]].\n\n==Sister Cities==\n{{unreferenced section|date=May 2018}}\n* [[Jinhua]], [[Zhejiang]]\n* {{flagdeco|HUN}} [[Szolnok]], Hungary\n* {{flagdeco|VNM}} [[Qu\u1ea3ng Nam Province]], Vietnam\n* {{flagdeco|AUT}} [[Vals, Austria|Vals]], Austria\n* {{flagdeco|FRA}} [[Provins]], [[\u00cele-de-France]], France\n* {{flagdeco|LAO}} [[Luang Prabang]], Laos\n\n== References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120920015227/http://www.sxjz.gov.cn/ Jinzhong City Portal]\n* [http://www.jinzhong.gov.cn/ - Jinzhong Information Network