 Bowl (Tempe)|Cactus Bowl]]\n| [[Tempe, Arizona]]\n| [[Pac-12 Conference|Pac-12]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"| 7\n| [[Heart of Dallas Bowl]]<sup>\u2021</sup>\n| [[Dallas|Dallas, Texas]] \n| [[Big Ten Conference]] \n|-\n|[[Armed Forces Bowl|Lockheed Martin Armed Forces Bowl]]<sup>\u2021</sup>\n|[[Fort Worth, Texas]]\n|[[American Athletic Conference|American]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"  style=\"font-size:8pt; text-align:center;\"|'''Reference:<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.big12sports.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=10410&ATCLID=211664582 | title = 2017 Big 12 Bowl Selection Process | publisher = Big 12 Conference }}</ref>'''\n|}\n\n<small><sup>\u2020</sup>:The Big 12 champion will go to the Sugar Bowl unless selected for the CFP. In the event that the conference champion is selected for the playoff, the conference runner up will go to the Sugar Bowl.<br/>\n<sup>\u2021</sup>:Conference representative will play in the bowls on a rotating basis.</small>\n\n==Final standings==\n\n{| cellpadding=\"5\"\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{1996 Big 12 football standings|normal=1}}\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{1997 Big 12 football standings|normal=1}}\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{1998 Big 12 football standings|normal=1}}\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{1999 Big 12 football standings|normal=1}}\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{2000 Big 12 football standings|normal=1}}\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{2001 Big 12 football standings|normal=1}}\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{2002 Big 12 football standings|normal=1}}\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{2003 Big 12 football standings|}}\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{2004 Big 12 football standings|normal=1}}\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{2005 Big 12 football standings|normal=1}}\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{2006 Big 12 football standings|normal=1}}\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{2007 Big 12 football standings|normal=1}}\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" width=25em|{{2008 Big 12 football standings|normal=1}}\n|valign=\"top\" width=2