ft;\"\n|-\n! style=\"text-align: center;\"| Pick\n!\n<center>Name</center>\n! style=\"text-align: center;\"| Location\n! style=\"text-align: center;\"| Opposing conference\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"| \u2013\n| [[College Football Playoff]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|\u2013\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|\u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"| 1\n| [[Sugar Bowl]]<sup>\u2020</sup>\n| [[New Orleans|New Orleans, Louisiana]]\n| [[Southeastern Conference|SEC]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"| 2\n| [[Alamo Bowl|Valero Alamo Bowl]]\n| [[San Antonio|San Antonio, Texas]]\n| [[Pac-12 Conference|Pac-12]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"| 3\n| [[Camping World Bowl]]\n| [[Orlando, Florida]]\n| [[Atlantic Coast Conference|ACC]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"| 4\n| [[Texas Bowl|AdvoCare V100 Texas Bowl]]\n| [[Houston|Houston, Texas]]\n| [[Southeastern Conference|SEC]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"| 5\n| [[Liberty Bowl|AutoZone Liberty Bowl]]\n| [[Memphis, Tennessee]]\n| [[Southeastern Conference|SEC]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"| 6\n| [[Cactus Bowl (Tempe)|Cactus Bowl]]\n| [[Tempe, Arizona]]\n| [[Pac-12 Conference|Pac-12]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"| 7\n| [[Heart of Dallas Bowl]]<sup>\u2021</sup>\n| [[Dallas|Dallas, Texas]] \n| [[Big Ten Conference]] \n|-\n|[[Armed Forces Bowl|Lockheed Martin Armed Forces Bowl]]<sup>\u2021</sup>\n|[[Fort Worth, Texas]]\n|[[American Athletic Conference|American]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"  style=\"font-size:8pt; text-align:center;\"|'''Reference:<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.big12sports.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=10410&ATCLID=211664582 | title = 2017 Big 12 Bowl Selection Process | publisher = Big 12 Conference }}</ref>'''\n|}\n\n<small><sup>\u2020</sup>:The Big 12 champion will go to the Sugar Bowl unless selected for the CFP. In the event that the conference champion is selected for the playoff, the conference runner up will go to the Sugar Bowl.<br/>\n<sup>\u2021</su